      "role": "user",
      "content": "wait, \"hexagonal cells\"? i've never heard of that being part of standard ATC procedures. why would they need to organize airspace into hexagons like that? it feels like it's doing more than just managing traffic... if they're tracing these specific shapes, what kind of effect would that actually have on the area below? like, if you have these intersecting electromagnetic paths, what does that do to the ground level?",
